---
title: Balsamic Rosemary Chicken with Garlic Toast & Green Beans
description: We believe pork chops are a canvas. Tonight’s palette for your palate: A saucy coating that includes fresh rosemary, tangy balsamic vinegar, and creamy garlic herb butter—because why choose one when you could have them all? Complement those chops with a side of garlic herb toast and roasted green beans, and you have yourself a dinner to Remem-brandt.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/645bda2951663d88c8044fb0-e8f41a59.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/balsamic-rosemary-chicken-645bda2951663d88c8044fb0-2122c660.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20m
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 650 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-rosemary-chicken-645bda2951663d88c8044fb0
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings).

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork; cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chopped rosemary; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), and @sugar{2%teaspoon} (4 tsp for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season generously with @pepper{}.

Turn off heat. Stir in half the @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} until melted (you'll use the rest in the next step).

Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise and toast; spread cut sides with remaining garlic herb butter. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Halve on a diagonal.

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, garlic bread, and green beans between plates. Top pork with balsamic rosemary pan sauce and serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.